column206: Hole told the story of the day. Flushed 5 iron right at my target just didn't move hit above bunker and hopped in. Chucked gap wedge from bunker decent chip par putt falls off just under the hole. Lack of consistency
Chunked 60 on approach

Weird lie on top of a bunker, not really able to get a stance. Hit 8 iron solid but into bunker. Chunked first sand shot under the lip, had to hit backwards into the bunker. Disappointing hole during a nice round
Great cut 9 iron just right of the flag about 4 feet at most. Great bounce back after disaster hole before

Disappointing 3 putt to end an overall nice round. Had good and bad was happy I found my swing on the back 9 but lost my putting feel. Became very tentative for some reason after a great front 9 on the green
Hit a fat 8 iron from the tea. Hit 60 from 100 yards on 2nd shot
Hit a fat 9 iron from bare lie in rough from 142. From fairway was able to get up and down with 60 from 68 yards
Flushed a cut 5 iron from the fairway to the back of the green
Just bad luck compounding on this hole. Hit every shot well except pin was in a tricky location. Above the hole after my chip for a short 3 putt.
Shanked 8 iron. Was weird, felt good over the ball
Lost focus i think on this one. Was 1 under to start the day after 2, and now 2 doubles in a row when nothing felt bad.  Was at a loss for what was happening
Hit a nice 7 iron that ended up over the green. Firm conditions
Flushed 6 iron, Was magnificent. Nate had just hit a beautiful 3w from 225 on in 2!
An unfortunate hole
Mental lapse forgot about the hole being on top the ridge and left it short. Made 3 footer for 5th putt
Made 25 foot putt from off the green
Couldn't find tee shot in rough. Took a drop because of it. Found it while playing 2, as it goes. Was in a much better spot and lie compared to my drop. Must have walked right by it
First  hole of the day. Took a breakfast ball,  first time this year :(
Hit a really nice 5 iron through the wind. Right where i aimeez just missed slightly left, flag on the top tier
Fun chip shot, went long last the hole on front tier up the backstop and used the slope to bring it back to the hole.
Thought I hit a good 60 into the green, just no way to hold it. Awful putting this hole
Made 20 foot par putt from the fringe. Barely off the green
Hit a nice 8 iron, just a slight tug into left bunker. Hit a solid bunker shot too
Nate flushed a 3 wood through the wind just left, right where he aimed, was hole high. Really great strike
Nate flushed a beautiful 5 iron off the tee. Unfortunate 3 putt. His approach shot was well struck too
Made a Brent.  Smothered duff tee shot par
Unfortunate 4 putt.  He didnt get it up the huge slope on his first putt.  I did the same the week prior

Crazy hole. Nate smashed a drive. He hawked a ball in a weird lie above the bunker.  We couldn't find his ball,  he realized hawked ball was his.  He actually swung and missed his 2nd shot. Barely hit 3rd which rolled down into bunker. Striped a 6 iron from bunker into face of the slope. Then drained 60 foot bogey save putt. Was incredible
First putt went off the green
